Why the other CD is rejected
- Mid‑focused, thick hard‑rock sound: The second candidate is explicitly “warm mid–focused mastering” with “thick, riff‑driven guitar/drum mixes” and “upfront gritty vocals.” Those characteristics match my stated dislikes: thick, mid‑forward hard‑rock mixes that can bury detail and upfront gritty vocals that reduce vocal nuance and clarity. Even though it “preserves dynamics,” the mid‑focus and thickness work against my preference for detail‑forward, clarity‑preserving masters.
- Album‑flow and extended solos: Candidate 2 emphasizes “intact full‑length tracks and tasteful extended solos” and “collector‑style packaging for album‑flow hard‑rock fans.” I said I no longer insist on full‑length solos or strict album‑flow and prefer momentum and single‑readiness. Extended solos and an album‑flow focus therefore make the second CD less aligned with my current priorities.
