Net assessment
- Queen – Greatest Hits 1 matches more of my core preferences: singles‑oriented tight sequencing, preserved transients and analog tonality without becoming muddy, clear vocal presence, and restrained overdubs that keep detail and headroom intact. The hard‑rock, mid‑forward profile and album‑flow emphasis of the second candidate conflict with several explicit dislikes, so it is the poorer fit for my stated listening and mastering preferences.

